                  <birth when="1902"/>
                  
                  
                  <floruit notBefore="1918" notAfter="1936">She was a daughter of 
                     <roleName type="title">rās</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS6665Mangasa"/> and a niece of <persName ref="PRS9345taytuBe"/>. 
                     She was an intelligent and well-educated woman, noted not least because of her three marriages. 
                     <persName ref="PRS9345taytuBe"/> arranged her marriage to 
                     <persName ref="PRS5620IyasuV"/> on <date>16 May 1909</date>.
                     Later she married also to <roleName type="title">rās</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS4624Getaccaw"/> in<date>1918</date> with whom she had two childern. 
                     After her divorce from <roleName type="title">rās</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS4624Getaccaw"/>, she married
                     <roleName type="title">bālāmbārās</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS2194Assabber"/>.</floruit>
